---
description: ESLint rules
globs: ["eslint/**", "eslint.config.mjs"]
---
- Flat config split by concern in /eslint, composed in eslint/index.mjs; prettier config last.
- Custom architecture plugin (eslint/architecture-plugin) enforces layer boundaries
  (no-restricted-layer-imports, controller-no-logic, repository-persistence-only), zero-inline
  definitions (no-inline-domain-definitions), env discipline (no-direct-env-access), and TSX
  purity (tsx-pure-composition).
- Vendor ownership is enforced via the package-boundaries registry (no-direct-sdk-imports +
  no-raw-library-imports): every third-party package maps to exactly one owning wrapper/adapter.
- Reusable definitions never live inline: types/interfaces/enums go to types/ (or model/, enums/),
  reusable value/config consts and `as const` maps go to constants/ (or model/).
- `no-inline-domain-definitions` now ALSO bans module-level value/config `const` in apps/api layer
  files (controllers, services, use-cases, repositories, adapters; api/application/infrastructure);
  exempt: function-valued consts, `new`/call-expression wiring (DI/factories), and the single
  approved `LOG_CONTEXT`/`LOG_PREFIX`. Scoped to apps/api so web `*.variants.ts` class bundles stay valid.
- Frontend mirrors this via `frontend-architecture/no-inline-declarations`: no module-level
  types/interfaces/enums or non-function consts in component/container/hook/service/gateway/query/route
  files; `*.variants.ts` is the approved home for design-system class-string bundles.
- Component splitting is enforced on `*.component.tsx`/`*.container.tsx` by `max-lines` (130),
  `max-lines-per-function` (60), and `react/jsx-max-depth` (eslint/frontend/component-size.config.mjs) —
  tighter than the repo-wide 300/80 base — so views split before a god-component forms. A `.component.tsx`
  is pure JSX: `no-hooks-in-components` + `no-inline-component-logic` forbid hooks, logic, `.map()`, and
  inline handlers; a view that must map lists or hold body vars is a CONTAINER instead.
- Never add eslint-disable; fix the code. Plugin relaxations must be documented in docs/eslint-architecture.md.
